    "setupGuide": {
      "title": "STACKIT setup",
      "steps": [{
        "step": 1,
        "title": "Get a STACKIT account and project",
        "description":
          "STACKIT is a B2B cloud by Schwarz Digital — request an organization at https://www.stackit.de, then create a project in the STACKIT Portal (https://portal.stackit.cloud).",
      }, {
        "step": 2,
        "title": "Create a service account with a key",
        "description":
          "In the Portal, open your project > Service Accounts, create one, assign it a role (e.g. reader), and create a service account key (key flow). The legacy static token flow was removed on 17 December 2025.",
      }, {
        "step": 3,
        "title": "Obtain a short-lived access token",
        "description":
          "Exchange a self-signed JWT (signed with the key's private RSA key) at the service account token endpoint, or simply run the STACKIT CLI: 'stackit auth activate-service-account --service-account-key-path key.json' and export the resulting access token.",
      }, {
        "step": 4,
        "title": "Set the environment variable",
        "description": "Put the access token into your .env as STACKIT_SERVICE_ACCOUNT_TOKEN.",
      }, {
        "step": 5,
        "title": "Verify access",
        "description":
          "Run List Projects with member set to the service account's email, then List Servers for a returned projectId in your region (e.g. eu01).",
      }],
      "notes": [
        "Access tokens from the key flow are short-lived (refresh roughly every 10 minutes) — automate token renewal for long-running agents",
        "List Projects requires at least one filter: containerParentId (organization/folder) or member (email)",
        "The IaaS API v2 is the stable release; v1 is deprecated and will be removed after 1 March 2027",
        "IaaS URLs are region-scoped via the {region} path segment, e.g. eu01",
      ],
      "documentation": "https://docs.stackit.cloud/developer-tools/stackit-api/",
    },
